main event: An observation of 2-3 unidentified objects was recorded near Olean, New York on April 16, 1960.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 30-35 minutes,The objects traveled in a northwesterly direction at an extremely high rate of speed,The objects appeared circular and presented no sound or visible trail when observed through binoculars,There was consideration that the sighting could have been a group of migrating waterfowl due to the time of year and observed characteristics,The incident was evaluated by ATIC which suggested the probable cause was birds, but did not reach a definitive conclusion.
witness description: Civil Defense Director and News Director for a local radio station, both described as reliable.
